{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"format-number","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions/format-number","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div style=\"background:#f5f5f5; margin: 5px 0;\" id=\"sect1\">\n    <b><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Transforming_XML_with_XSLT/The_Netscape_XSLT_XPath_Reference\">XSLT/XPath Reference</a></b>: <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element\">XSLT elements</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/EXSLT\">EXSLT functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions\">XPath functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Axes\">XPath axes</a>\n</div>\n<p>The <code>format-number</code> function evaluates a number and returns a string representing the number in a given format.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":true,"content":"<pre class=\"notranslate\">format-number( number, pattern [,decimal-format] )\n</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"arguments","title":"Arguments","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"number\"><code>number</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The number to be formatted</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"pattern\"><code>pattern</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A string in the format of the <a href=\"https://java.sun.com/products/archive/jdk/1.1/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">JDK 1.1</a> DecimalFormat class. (The documentation for JDK 1.1 is not available online. Here is the <a href=\"https://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/text/DecimalFormat.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Java SE 6 DecimalFormat</a>.)</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"decimal-format\"><code>decimal-format</code> (optional)</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The name of an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element/decimal-format\"><code>xsl:decimal-format</code></a> element that defines the number format to be used. If omitted, the default decimal-format will be used.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"returns","title":"Returns","isH3":true,"content":"<p>A string representing the number in the new format.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notes","title":"Notes","isH3":true,"content":"<p>This function is an XSLT-specific addition to XPath. It is not a part of the core XPath function library.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"defined","title":"Defined","isH3":true,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/xslt#function-format-number\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">XSLT 1.0 12.3</a></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"gecko_support","title":"Gecko support","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Supported.</p>"}}],"toc":[],"summary":"The format-number function evaluates a number and returns a string representing the number in a given format.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-01-19T10:53:25.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"format-number","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"format-number","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"format-number","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"format-number","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/xpath/functions/format-number","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/xpath/functions/format-number/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/44ca1647c2a36f955203584addd724a193a614a9","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath","title":"XPath"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions","title":"Functions"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions/format-number","title":"format-number"}],"pageTitle":"format-number - XPath | MDN","noIndexing":false}}